HTML - Hyper text Markup language

- To create the Web pages
- Its not a programming language
- Its a Markup Language
- Every website can start with HTML

1. Heading - h is h1 to h6

2. Paragraph - p

3. Hr

4. br

5. Text Formatting - b or strong, u, mark, Sub and Sup......

6. Anchor tag - a

7. Image tag - img

8. list - Order list and unorder list

9. tables - tr, th, td

10. Forms - Input and label

11. Sematic tags - header, footer, section, nav and main

12. Media Elements
    Audio and Video

CSS - Cascading Style Sheet

1. Types of CSS
   i - Inline
   ii - Internal
   iii - External
   inline > internal > external

2. CSS Syntax
   selector{
   property: value;
   }

3. Types of Selector
   i - Element selector - (h1) , (h2), (p)
   ii - Class selector - (.) Multiple time we can use that name
   iii - Id selector - (#) unique only one time we can use that name
   iv - Universal selector - (\*) to apply the entire site.
   v - Group selector - same class or id name and different tags can change the same style we use group selector.

4. Colors and background
   background-color: red;
   color: white;
   background-image: url(./Assets/Spider-Man.jpg);
   background-repeat: no-repeat;
   background-size: cover;
   background-position: center;

5. Text Styling
   font-family: Impact, Haettenschweiler, 'Arial Narrow Bold', sans-serif;
   font-size: 40px;
   text-align: center;
   text-transform: uppercase;
   text-decoration: underline;
   font-weight: 100;
   line-height: 1;
   letter-spacing: 1px;

6. Box Modeling
   margin
   border
   padding
   content

7. Flex (Display)
  1. Direction - row, row-reverse, column, column-reverse
  2. Justify-content - (X) - start, center, end, space-around, space-evenly, space-between
  3. Align-items - (Y) - start, end, center
  4. Flex-wrap - wrap and wrap-reverse
  5. Align-content - (Y) (only flex wrap is enable then only align-content will work) -  start, center, end, space-around, space-evenly, space-between
  6. Flex(on items) - flex-1 - if you want to grow then we go with flex-1
  7. order - Change the Visual order of the flex items
  8. Gap - to give the values like Px,cm,m,%....

8. Position
  1. Static (default)
  2. Relative
  3. Absolute
  4. Fixed
  5. Sticky

9. Grid 
  2 - dimensional layout system
  
10. Transition and Animation
   Transition - Whenever you hover that it will act
   Animation - Just Refresh the sit the changes will act

11. Media Queries or Responsive Design
  Mobile      - 320px to 600px
  tab         - 601px to 800px
  lap/desktop - above 801px